Ships searching the vast Indian Ocean for a Malaysian airliner have detected three separate underwater signals, and more ships and planes were diverted Sunday to investigate whether they could have come from its "black box". Staff from Phoenix International test the functionality of the Artemis autonomous underwater vehicle on the deck of the Australian ship Ocean Shield as it searches for missing Malaysia Airlines flight MH370 in the southern Indian Ocean, April 1, 2014Angus Houston, head of the Australian search mission, said the detections were being taken "very seriously" as time ticked down on the battery life of the black box's tracking beacons. This article is older than 60 days, which we reserve for our premium members only. You can subscribe to our premium member subscription, here. 